1
00:00:36,110 --> 00:00:41,240
♪In rain or shine♪

2
00:00:41,780 --> 00:00:46,870
♪When you're around,
the sun shines through♪

3
00:00:47,220 --> 00:00:52,640
♪Spare ourselves the endless thoughts
and guessing games♪

4
00:00:52,930 --> 00:00:58,880
♪Let's just meet
and escape these frames♪

5
00:00:59,360 --> 00:01:02,600
♪I stand within the shadows deep♪

6
00:01:02,880 --> 00:01:08,030
♪My hand outstretched,
your rescue I keep♪

7
00:01:08,220 --> 00:01:12,850
♪Even if the world falls apart♪

8
00:01:13,170 --> 00:01:15,870
♪No distance is too far♪

9
00:01:17,260 --> 00:01:21,390
♪To stop us from coming together♪

10
00:01:21,720 --> 00:01:27,710
♪Through the night,
you're at the end of the line♪

11
00:01:28,710 --> 00:01:32,730
♪To protect you is my humble wish♪

12
00:01:32,920 --> 00:01:36,920
♪Farewell, to the timid soul I knew♪

13
00:01:37,270 --> 00:01:42,550
♪It was you who made me brave and new♪

14
00:01:42,550 --> 00:01:46,180
=Always Home=
(Adapted from Xiao Ge's novel, Always Home)

15
00:01:46,260 --> 00:01:49,180
=Episode 17=
(So This Is How You Play?)

16
00:01:52,380 --> 00:01:53,890
For all these shampoos and other stuff,

17
00:01:53,890 --> 00:01:54,860
I let Huan'er bring them.

18
00:01:54,860 --> 00:01:55,900
Buy two more bottles later.

19
00:01:55,900 --> 00:01:57,470
Close it tightly,
so they don't leak.

20
00:01:57,470 --> 00:01:58,220
Dad, Mom,

21
00:01:58,220 --> 00:01:58,750
I'm home!

22
00:01:58,750 --> 00:01:59,560
My dear, you're back.

23
00:01:59,560 --> 00:02:00,060
You're back.

24
00:02:02,500 --> 00:02:03,300
My dear girl,

25
00:02:03,390 --> 00:02:04,750
you've become slimmer.

26
00:02:05,060 --> 00:02:07,200
- Have you been too tired lately?
- No, I haven't.

27
00:02:07,420 --> 00:02:08,460
Why do I think she...

28
00:02:08,460 --> 00:02:10,300
Mom, what are you doing?

29
00:02:11,180 --> 00:02:12,790
See, your mom is so forgetful.

30
00:02:12,800 --> 00:02:14,280
Your admission letter already arrived,

31
00:02:14,280 --> 00:02:15,230
and I just remembered

32
00:02:15,240 --> 00:02:16,600
to get things ready for you.

33
00:02:16,680 --> 00:02:18,420
Oh, right. You have to report
on the 28th.

34
00:02:18,700 --> 00:02:19,700
So soon?

35
00:02:19,990 --> 00:02:20,790
Here, you see.

36
00:02:24,420 --> 00:02:26,300
(Wuan University)

37
00:02:26,300 --> 00:02:27,550
(Jing Xichi, how about you?)

38
00:02:28,820 --> 00:02:29,790
(I'm the same as Song.)

39
00:02:31,300 --> 00:02:32,580
What about your second choice?

40
00:02:32,580 --> 00:02:34,020
I didn't fill up a second choice.

41
00:02:34,390 --> 00:02:35,180
You didn't?

42
00:02:35,620 --> 00:02:36,830
How bold you are!

43
00:02:37,300 --> 00:02:38,350
What if

44
00:02:38,350 --> 00:02:39,070
you don't get in?

45
00:02:39,510 --> 00:02:40,140
What else?

46
00:02:40,360 --> 00:02:41,390
I'll just retake it.

47
00:02:41,830 --> 00:02:43,020
Retake your head!

48
00:02:43,670 --> 00:02:44,670
You know how struggling

49
00:02:44,740 --> 00:02:45,580
this year was.

50
00:02:48,790 --> 00:02:49,420
What's wrong?

51
00:02:50,350 --> 00:02:50,990
Not happy?

52
00:02:51,100 --> 00:02:53,180
Do you think the stuff Dad bought
is old-fashioned?

53
00:02:53,180 --> 00:02:54,600
He doesn't have an eye for fashion.

54
00:02:54,600 --> 00:02:55,380
Doesn't look good?

55
00:02:55,380 --> 00:02:56,460
I can get you something else.

56
00:02:56,460 --> 00:02:57,230
No, Dad.

57
00:02:59,990 --> 00:03:01,390
I just feel that...

58
00:03:01,830 --> 00:03:03,230
I'm going to university.

59
00:03:03,360 --> 00:03:04,580
Leaving home to another city,

60
00:03:05,180 --> 00:03:06,230
being away from friends

61
00:03:06,270 --> 00:03:07,670
and parents...

62
00:03:08,390 --> 00:03:10,270
I feel a bit reluctant.

63
00:03:11,670 --> 00:03:13,550
Tianhe isn't far from Wuan.

64
00:03:13,580 --> 00:03:15,740
That's just less than
an hour away by high-speed rail.

65
00:03:15,740 --> 00:03:17,280
If you're homesick,
come back every week.

66
00:03:17,280 --> 00:03:17,580
Yeah.

67
00:03:18,070 --> 00:03:18,990
When I have time,

68
00:03:19,060 --> 00:03:20,230
I'll visit you whenever I can.

69
00:03:20,990 --> 00:03:21,580
Huan'er,

70
00:03:21,860 --> 00:03:23,070
your mom is right.

71
00:03:23,300 --> 00:03:24,670
Just come back if you miss home.

72
00:03:24,790 --> 00:03:25,700
If it gets too hard,

73
00:03:25,700 --> 00:03:27,300
it's fine for not going to university.

74
00:03:27,380 --> 00:03:27,950
Dad!

75
00:03:28,020 --> 00:03:30,270
Can you wish me something good for once?

76
00:03:34,070 --> 00:03:34,900
Oh, yeah, Mom.

77
00:03:35,300 --> 00:03:36,270
Has Jing Xichi

78
00:03:36,270 --> 00:03:37,680
received his admission letter yet?

79
00:03:38,950 --> 00:03:39,740
I don't know.

80
00:03:39,900 --> 00:03:40,830
I do.

81
00:03:41,350 --> 00:03:42,300
How do you know?

82
00:03:42,550 --> 00:03:43,510
I saw it.

83
00:03:43,510 --> 00:03:45,390
A delivery man went
to their house a few days ago

84
00:03:45,390 --> 00:03:46,550
and delivered them a letter.

85
00:03:46,740 --> 00:03:48,270
You've got sharp eyes.

86
00:03:48,860 --> 00:03:50,180
What do you mean?

87
00:04:26,900 --> 00:04:28,200
(Congratulations to you)

88
00:04:28,380 --> 00:04:30,150
(that you got into
your dream university.)

89
00:04:30,820 --> 00:04:32,110
(I also received the offer letter)

90
00:04:32,110 --> 00:04:33,300
(from Wuan University.)

91
00:04:33,700 --> 00:04:37,300
(Messaging)

92
00:04:40,280 --> 00:04:42,200
(Recipients: Song Cong,
Piggy Jing, Princess 7)

93
00:04:42,220 --> 00:04:44,100
(Editing Recipients)

94
00:04:44,100 --> 00:04:47,140
(Editing Recipients. Song Cong.)

95
00:04:47,140 --> 00:04:48,700
(Delete. Select.)

96
00:04:48,700 --> 00:04:49,780
(Song Cong. Delete? Yes.)

97
00:04:49,780 --> 00:04:51,460
(Editing Recipients:
Piggy Jing, Princess 7)

98
00:04:53,200 --> 00:04:54,840
(Messaging.
Recipients: Piggy Jing, Princess 7)

99
00:04:54,860 --> 00:04:55,940
(Sending messages)

100
00:05:00,940 --> 00:05:02,110
(Want to meet up?)

101
00:05:02,470 --> 00:05:03,790
(I think celebrating in person)

102
00:05:03,790 --> 00:05:04,710
(is more meaningful.)

103
00:05:06,180 --> 00:05:07,900
(Recipient: Piggy Jing)

104
00:05:23,790 --> 00:05:24,740
Why are you here?

105
00:05:27,180 --> 00:05:29,150
I was bored at home

106
00:05:30,060 --> 00:05:31,380
as I had nothing to do,

107
00:05:31,910 --> 00:05:33,060
so I came to find you.

108
00:05:35,260 --> 00:05:37,030
How was your graduation trip?

109
00:05:41,300 --> 00:05:41,940
It was fine.

110
00:05:45,260 --> 00:05:46,590
I can tell from your response

111
00:05:47,860 --> 00:05:49,230
that it was not fine.

112
00:05:50,110 --> 00:05:51,470
Luckily, I decided not to go.

113
00:05:52,150 --> 00:05:52,910
I knew

114
00:05:53,110 --> 00:05:54,790
that it was a waste of money to suffer.

115
00:05:57,300 --> 00:05:58,790
All of you

116
00:05:59,670 --> 00:06:00,590
are too complicated.

117
00:06:01,720 --> 00:06:02,500
With that time,

118
00:06:02,500 --> 00:06:03,940
I'd rather study.

119
00:06:05,060 --> 00:06:06,860
Yeah, it's so complicated.

120
00:06:10,740 --> 00:06:11,230
I...

121
00:06:16,940 --> 00:06:17,590
Never mind.

122
00:06:18,110 --> 00:06:18,990
You should go home.

123
00:06:19,110 --> 00:06:19,910
I'm closing up.

124
00:06:22,910 --> 00:06:23,590
Fine.

125
00:06:24,150 --> 00:06:24,790
Alright.

126
00:06:25,060 --> 00:06:26,230
I'll come by tomorrow.

127
00:06:27,150 --> 00:06:28,820
Don't come here tomorrow.

128
00:06:28,910 --> 00:06:30,180
I won't be here tomorrow.

129
00:06:31,740 --> 00:06:33,550
I have a tutoring job tomorrow.

130
00:07:15,740 --> 00:07:16,420
Huan'er.

131
00:07:24,790 --> 00:07:25,550
Song Cong.

132
00:07:27,620 --> 00:07:29,940
Why are you here?

133
00:07:32,300 --> 00:07:34,150
I just came out to get some air.

134
00:07:42,380 --> 00:07:43,350
Congratulations

135
00:07:44,380 --> 00:07:46,320
that you got into Yenching University.

136
00:07:48,380 --> 00:07:49,260
Thanks.

137
00:07:51,100 --> 00:07:52,460
Congratulations to you too.

138
00:07:53,470 --> 00:07:54,180
Thank you.

139
00:07:57,500 --> 00:07:58,860
I was just watering the plants.

140
00:07:59,260 --> 00:08:00,550
I get to go now.

141
00:08:01,550 --> 00:08:02,150
Huan'er.

142
00:08:12,670 --> 00:08:13,670
Stop avoiding me.

143
00:08:22,180 --> 00:08:23,030
I think

144
00:08:24,110 --> 00:08:24,820
there are things

145
00:08:25,300 --> 00:08:26,670
I should clarify to you.

146
00:08:37,710 --> 00:08:39,190
I want to apologize to you.

147
00:08:44,430 --> 00:08:45,900
What I said that day

148
00:08:47,190 --> 00:08:48,900
must have made things awkward for you.

149
00:08:50,430 --> 00:08:51,070
I...

150
00:08:51,470 --> 00:08:53,140
I drank too much that day

151
00:08:55,070 --> 00:08:56,350
and I got a little carried away.

152
00:08:59,020 --> 00:08:59,780
It's fine.

153
00:09:02,620 --> 00:09:04,430
You don't have to apologize for that.

154
00:09:09,310 --> 00:09:10,470
Just pretend I never say that.

155
00:09:14,710 --> 00:09:15,540
Well...

156
00:09:16,860 --> 00:09:17,780
Can we

157
00:09:20,190 --> 00:09:21,310
still be friends after this?

158
00:09:41,430 --> 00:09:42,660
Honestly...

159
00:09:43,900 --> 00:09:45,260
It's hard for now.

160
00:09:48,020 --> 00:09:50,190
Please give me some time

161
00:09:50,950 --> 00:09:52,110
to process.

162
00:09:57,780 --> 00:09:58,380
Alright.

163
00:09:59,950 --> 00:10:00,500
It's okay.

164
00:10:01,500 --> 00:10:02,470
If you feel

165
00:10:03,230 --> 00:10:04,140
it's awkward,

166
00:10:04,140 --> 00:10:04,900
you can just

167
00:10:06,380 --> 00:10:07,540
think of me

168
00:10:07,860 --> 00:10:08,620
as a neighbor.

169
00:10:18,070 --> 00:10:20,590
I'm leaving.

170
00:11:20,780 --> 00:11:21,950
(I'm at our secret base.)

171
00:11:22,430 --> 00:11:23,500
(Do you want to come?)

172
00:11:39,460 --> 00:11:40,660
(I'm working on the website.)

173
00:11:40,990 --> 00:11:41,780
(I'm not going.)

174
00:12:02,230 --> 00:12:02,860
Sit here.

175
00:12:02,990 --> 00:12:03,430
Alright.

176
00:12:03,760 --> 00:12:05,020
I'll go and order some drinks.

177
00:12:05,430 --> 00:12:06,110
What do you want?

178
00:12:06,190 --> 00:12:07,080
Anything is fine.

179
00:12:08,380 --> 00:12:09,380
Hello, waiter.

180
00:12:09,590 --> 00:12:10,070
Hi.

181
00:12:10,070 --> 00:12:11,470
Three orange juices, please.

182
00:12:11,620 --> 00:12:12,140
Thank you.

183
00:12:15,780 --> 00:12:16,500
Huan'er,

184
00:12:16,900 --> 00:12:17,860
how do you resist

185
00:12:17,860 --> 00:12:19,140
buying all those

186
00:12:19,140 --> 00:12:20,260
pretty dresses?

187
00:12:21,110 --> 00:12:22,740
I feel like none of the stores

188
00:12:22,780 --> 00:12:24,350
have one that suits me.

189
00:12:25,660 --> 00:12:26,540
Which one do you think

190
00:12:27,180 --> 00:12:28,470
looks better? Is this gray one

191
00:12:29,020 --> 00:12:30,110
or the white one

192
00:12:30,110 --> 00:12:31,020
that I didn't buy?

193
00:12:31,590 --> 00:12:32,350
White...

194
00:12:36,190 --> 00:12:37,710
I think they both look nice.

195
00:12:38,470 --> 00:12:39,540
They look the same to me.

196
00:12:40,950 --> 00:12:41,740
I think

197
00:12:41,830 --> 00:12:43,230
white is more elegant.

198
00:12:44,070 --> 00:12:45,190
And I feel like

199
00:12:45,310 --> 00:12:45,990
my boyfriend

200
00:12:46,020 --> 00:12:47,230
likes that style more too.

201
00:12:49,470 --> 00:12:50,950
You have a boyfriend?

202
00:12:53,740 --> 00:12:54,310
Xinyan!

203
00:12:54,590 --> 00:12:55,140
Babe!

204
00:12:56,540 --> 00:12:57,660
I'm sorry. There was a long

205
00:12:57,740 --> 00:12:58,860
line in the ice cream store

206
00:12:58,900 --> 00:12:59,780
where I bought this.

207
00:12:59,860 --> 00:13:00,880
Sorry to keep you waiting.

208
00:13:00,880 --> 00:13:01,640
Thank you.

209
00:13:02,190 --> 00:13:03,230
Oops, sorry.

210
00:13:03,280 --> 00:13:04,540
You have a friend with you here.

211
00:13:04,950 --> 00:13:05,950
I only bought one.

212
00:13:06,140 --> 00:13:08,140
I'll go and buy another for your friend.

213
00:13:08,180 --> 00:13:09,140
That's so sweet of you.

214
00:13:09,310 --> 00:13:10,140
It's so hot outside.

215
00:13:10,350 --> 00:13:11,950
It's fine. Not a big deal.

216
00:13:12,190 --> 00:13:13,540
Just wait for me a while.

217
00:13:14,070 --> 00:13:14,710
Wait a minute.

218
00:13:15,710 --> 00:13:16,470
Help me pick.

219
00:13:16,470 --> 00:13:17,490
Which dress looks better?

220
00:13:17,590 --> 00:13:18,860
Gray or white?

221
00:13:19,230 --> 00:13:20,780
I love them both and I can't decide.

222
00:13:22,460 --> 00:13:23,350
They both look great.

223
00:13:23,540 --> 00:13:24,500
If you like them both,

224
00:13:24,540 --> 00:13:25,470
just buy them both.

225
00:13:25,860 --> 00:13:26,540
I'll pay for it.

226
00:13:26,740 --> 00:13:28,140
I'm not that greedy.

227
00:13:28,540 --> 00:13:29,430
They are similar.

228
00:13:29,470 --> 00:13:30,430
One is enough.

229
00:13:31,000 --> 00:13:32,190
You go and buy the ice cream.

230
00:13:32,240 --> 00:13:33,600
I have another friend coming later.

231
00:13:33,600 --> 00:13:34,200
Get one more.

232
00:13:35,990 --> 00:13:36,470
Alright.

233
00:13:42,310 --> 00:13:43,350
Chen Huan'er!

234
00:13:43,430 --> 00:13:44,780
What's with that face?

235
00:13:45,110 --> 00:13:46,380
Nothing.

236
00:13:47,140 --> 00:13:47,830
Huan'er!

237
00:13:47,900 --> 00:13:48,380
Xinyan!

238
00:13:48,620 --> 00:13:49,710
Why are you so late?

239
00:13:49,720 --> 00:13:50,950
I just finished my piano lesson

240
00:13:50,980 --> 00:13:52,020
and came straight here.

241
00:13:52,260 --> 00:13:52,990
Did you see

242
00:13:52,990 --> 00:13:53,980
my boyfriend just now?

243
00:13:54,080 --> 00:13:55,340
- What?
- Is he handsome?

244
00:13:55,340 --> 00:13:56,280
She has a boyfriend now.

245
00:13:56,320 --> 00:13:57,700
The one who just walked out.

246
00:13:58,860 --> 00:13:59,740
Boyfriend?

247
00:14:02,740 --> 00:14:03,740
Why this expression?

248
00:14:03,780 --> 00:14:04,620
Is it strange for me

249
00:14:04,710 --> 00:14:05,860
to have a boyfriend?

250
00:14:06,110 --> 00:14:07,140
Not strange.

251
00:14:07,990 --> 00:14:08,900
Just...

252
00:14:10,020 --> 00:14:11,500
Just a little too fast.

253
00:14:12,230 --> 00:14:13,900
I got rejected three days ago.

254
00:14:14,110 --> 00:14:15,260
Just three days?

255
00:14:18,020 --> 00:14:19,070
Are you

256
00:14:19,190 --> 00:14:20,830
getting upset

257
00:14:20,900 --> 00:14:22,480
because you got rejected by Jing Xichi,

258
00:14:22,480 --> 00:14:23,720
and you want to get back at him?

259
00:14:23,720 --> 00:14:24,840
How is that possible?

260
00:14:25,140 --> 00:14:26,860
I like my boyfriend very much.

261
00:14:27,950 --> 00:14:28,590
Then...

262
00:14:29,020 --> 00:14:30,230
When did you meet

263
00:14:30,310 --> 00:14:31,190
your boyfriend?

264
00:14:31,470 --> 00:14:32,020
Yesterday.

265
00:14:32,310 --> 00:14:33,070
Yesterday?

266
00:14:34,990 --> 00:14:36,190
On a soccer field.

267
00:14:36,380 --> 00:14:37,430
It was love at first sight.

268
00:14:39,500 --> 00:14:40,620
Soccer field?

269
00:14:40,860 --> 00:14:41,780
So...

270
00:14:43,140 --> 00:14:44,190
He's a substitute?

271
00:14:44,950 --> 00:14:45,830
How should I put it...

272
00:14:46,020 --> 00:14:46,950
Not exactly.

273
00:14:47,350 --> 00:14:48,230
I thought about it,

274
00:14:48,950 --> 00:14:50,990
and I just like

275
00:14:51,190 --> 00:14:52,710
this kind of athletic guy.

276
00:14:59,140 --> 00:14:59,540
So,

277
00:15:00,190 --> 00:15:01,660
do you still like Jing Xichi?

278
00:15:01,860 --> 00:15:02,590
Yes, I do.

279
00:15:04,190 --> 00:15:05,590
You like them both?

280
00:15:06,540 --> 00:15:08,190
It's just like with these dresses.

281
00:15:08,350 --> 00:15:09,500
I like them both,

282
00:15:09,660 --> 00:15:10,780
just in different colors.

283
00:15:11,380 --> 00:15:13,110
If circumstances allowed,

284
00:15:13,590 --> 00:15:15,310
I'd want them both.

285
00:15:15,830 --> 00:15:16,830
That sounds

286
00:15:18,950 --> 00:15:20,260
reasonable...

287
00:15:21,190 --> 00:15:23,190
How can this be reasonable?

288
00:15:24,260 --> 00:15:25,950
Dresses and people aren't the same.

289
00:15:26,140 --> 00:15:27,500
Why not?

290
00:15:27,950 --> 00:15:29,350
Are you planning

291
00:15:29,350 --> 00:15:32,070
to be hung up on Song Cong forever?

292
00:15:32,310 --> 00:15:33,430
You...

293
00:15:33,830 --> 00:15:34,470
How did you...

294
00:15:34,830 --> 00:15:36,540
You're way too obvious about Song Cong.

295
00:15:40,590 --> 00:15:41,620
I don't know.

296
00:15:42,230 --> 00:15:43,140
But,

297
00:15:43,860 --> 00:15:45,140
Song Cong doesn't like me.

298
00:15:46,110 --> 00:15:46,900
There's nothing

299
00:15:46,900 --> 00:15:48,070
between us.

300
00:15:48,590 --> 00:15:49,140
Qi Qi,

301
00:15:49,190 --> 00:15:50,430
I already made things clear

302
00:15:50,470 --> 00:15:51,350
with him that day.

303
00:15:51,380 --> 00:15:53,260
I knew something was
going on between you two.

304
00:15:53,260 --> 00:15:55,140
I could tell
from the agriculture study lesson.

305
00:15:55,140 --> 00:15:56,540
No, there's nothing!

306
00:15:57,190 --> 00:15:57,740
Qi Qi,

307
00:15:57,900 --> 00:15:59,260
don't misunderstand me.

308
00:15:59,310 --> 00:16:00,740
I made it clear to him.

309
00:16:01,070 --> 00:16:02,310
Don't worry.

310
00:16:02,400 --> 00:16:04,280
Whether Song Cong
likes or doesn't like you,

311
00:16:04,320 --> 00:16:05,440
or whoever he likes,

312
00:16:05,500 --> 00:16:07,320
you will always be
my most important friend.

313
00:16:08,590 --> 00:16:11,470
So, since there's nothing
between you and Song Cong...

314
00:16:11,740 --> 00:16:13,950
Doesn't that mean you have a chance?

315
00:16:14,260 --> 00:16:15,020
Me?

316
00:16:15,740 --> 00:16:16,430
Think about it.

317
00:16:16,620 --> 00:16:18,020
For four years of university life,

318
00:16:18,540 --> 00:16:20,900
you two are far away from home

319
00:16:21,540 --> 00:16:22,590
with parents not around

320
00:16:22,590 --> 00:16:23,310
to watch over you,

321
00:16:24,040 --> 00:16:25,540
and there will be plenty of chances

322
00:16:25,540 --> 00:16:27,110
you two study together.

323
00:16:27,860 --> 00:16:28,500
Isn't that

324
00:16:28,500 --> 00:16:29,190
your opportunity?

325
00:16:30,470 --> 00:16:31,260
Tell me more.

326
00:16:33,500 --> 00:16:34,430
First,

327
00:16:35,460 --> 00:16:36,920
you have to take the initiative.

328
00:16:37,070 --> 00:16:37,990
In Year 1,

329
00:16:38,310 --> 00:16:39,780
you need to seize the moment.

330
00:16:39,990 --> 00:16:41,700
Well, how does she take the initiative?

331
00:16:42,470 --> 00:16:43,540
Make sure he knows

332
00:16:43,990 --> 00:16:45,230
you like him.

333
00:16:45,430 --> 00:16:46,830
He already knows.

334
00:16:47,140 --> 00:16:48,190
Then, you're halfway there.

335
00:16:49,590 --> 00:16:50,900
That's already halfway?

336
00:16:51,900 --> 00:16:52,740
So,

337
00:16:53,160 --> 00:16:54,580
what about the other half?

338
00:16:55,990 --> 00:16:57,020
Since you two are serious

339
00:16:57,020 --> 00:16:58,070
about learning this,

340
00:16:58,590 --> 00:17:00,110
I'll share my unbeatable

341
00:17:00,140 --> 00:17:01,140
dating strategies

342
00:17:01,380 --> 00:17:02,350
with you.

343
00:17:02,600 --> 00:17:04,190
Xinyan, stop keeping us in suspense.

344
00:17:04,230 --> 00:17:05,150
Just tell us.

345
00:17:06,150 --> 00:17:08,260
No desire means strength.

346
00:17:09,780 --> 00:17:10,670
The ice cream is here.

347
00:17:10,780 --> 00:17:11,390
Thanks, babe.

348
00:17:11,500 --> 00:17:12,340
This is my boyfriend.

349
00:17:12,540 --> 00:17:15,060
This is my friend Qi Qi,
and this is Huan'er. You just saw her.

350
00:17:15,120 --> 00:17:16,820
Nice to meet you.

351
00:17:16,820 --> 00:17:18,100
Don't just sit there. Try it.

352
00:17:18,840 --> 00:17:19,540
Let me feed you.

353
00:17:26,630 --> 00:17:27,300
Is it sweet?

354
00:17:28,780 --> 00:17:29,260
Sweet?

355
00:17:30,870 --> 00:17:31,580
Want another bite?

356
00:17:38,060 --> 00:17:39,150
Dad, Mom.

357
00:17:40,440 --> 00:17:41,340
You're back, my dear.

358
00:17:41,340 --> 00:17:41,870
You're back.

359
00:17:42,020 --> 00:17:42,740
I'm hungry.

360
00:17:42,780 --> 00:17:43,990
What did you guys make?

361
00:17:44,460 --> 00:17:46,200
We thought you wouldn't
be eating at home,

362
00:17:46,200 --> 00:17:47,660
so your dad and I just mixed everything

363
00:17:47,660 --> 00:17:49,580
and made a cold dish,
and some Zhajiangmian.

364
00:17:49,600 --> 00:17:50,820
Come, let's eat together.

365
00:17:51,870 --> 00:17:52,540
Is this enough?

366
00:17:52,540 --> 00:17:53,380
It smells so good.

367
00:17:53,380 --> 00:17:54,260
Is it okay?

368
00:17:54,580 --> 00:17:56,710
How could this not be okay, Mom?

369
00:17:57,100 --> 00:17:59,580
I was planning to eat out
with my classmates,

370
00:17:59,670 --> 00:18:00,540
but then I thought,

371
00:18:00,540 --> 00:18:02,020
since university is starting soon,

372
00:18:02,040 --> 00:18:04,500
I should enjoy more
of my mom's homemade food.

373
00:18:04,740 --> 00:18:06,710
What a liar!

374
00:18:08,240 --> 00:18:09,950
Your classmates must've had other plans

375
00:18:09,950 --> 00:18:11,230
and didn't invite you.

376
00:18:12,780 --> 00:18:13,540
How did you know?

377
00:18:13,740 --> 00:18:15,630
Is it that they had a date

378
00:18:15,670 --> 00:18:17,910
and didn't want you to be a third wheel?

379
00:18:18,390 --> 00:18:18,870
Dad!

380
00:18:19,340 --> 00:18:21,060
Mom must've put a GPS on me.

381
00:18:21,230 --> 00:18:22,870
I just simply guess.

382
00:18:23,150 --> 00:18:23,630
Wait, wait.

383
00:18:23,630 --> 00:18:24,760
What does it mean, Huan'er?

384
00:18:24,920 --> 00:18:26,150
Your classmates started dating?

385
00:18:26,870 --> 00:18:27,260
Yeah.

386
00:18:27,260 --> 00:18:28,300
No need to act so shocked.

387
00:18:28,300 --> 00:18:29,710
They'll be university students soon.

388
00:18:29,710 --> 00:18:30,870
What's wrong with dating?

389
00:18:30,940 --> 00:18:32,880
No. What do you mean
by “what's wrong with it”?

390
00:18:32,920 --> 00:18:34,710
Huan'er is still a young lady.

391
00:18:34,950 --> 00:18:36,150
Huan'er, listen to your dad.

392
00:18:36,340 --> 00:18:37,000
In university,

393
00:18:37,000 --> 00:18:39,020
the most important thing is
to focus on your studies,

394
00:18:39,020 --> 00:18:40,140
not on starting a date soon.

395
00:18:40,140 --> 00:18:41,240
I absolutely won't allow it.

396
00:18:41,240 --> 00:18:41,990
Don't listen to him.

397
00:18:42,060 --> 00:18:42,740
I tell you,

398
00:18:43,060 --> 00:18:44,300
it's your university life.

399
00:18:44,430 --> 00:18:45,580
It lasts four years.

400
00:18:45,710 --> 00:18:46,910
Why not enjoy your youth?

401
00:18:47,040 --> 00:18:48,950
Hold on, don't feed her
with all this thought,

402
00:18:49,020 --> 00:18:49,670
okay?

403
00:18:49,680 --> 00:18:51,260
What do you mean by enjoying the youth?

404
00:18:51,260 --> 00:18:52,670
What do you mean by that?

405
00:18:52,760 --> 00:18:53,910
When I was in medical school,

406
00:18:53,910 --> 00:18:55,640
weren't you who always
appeared in my school

407
00:18:55,640 --> 00:18:56,390
and chased after me?

408
00:18:56,390 --> 00:18:57,600
During your postgraduate years!

409
00:18:57,620 --> 00:18:58,360
Don't mess around.

410
00:18:58,360 --> 00:18:59,640
She's just in her freshman year.

411
00:18:59,740 --> 00:19:00,670
You're unbelievable.

412
00:19:00,670 --> 00:19:01,710
Absolutely no dating!

413
00:19:15,840 --> 00:19:16,990
Let me ask you something.

414
00:19:18,230 --> 00:19:19,710
Someone likes your classmates.

415
00:19:19,870 --> 00:19:21,360
Does anyone in your class like you?

416
00:19:22,430 --> 00:19:23,060
Chen Huan'er,

417
00:19:24,100 --> 00:19:24,740
I like you.

418
00:19:27,060 --> 00:19:28,300
No one...

419
00:19:28,470 --> 00:19:30,230
How could anyone like me?

420
00:19:30,470 --> 00:19:31,190
It makes sense.

421
00:19:31,190 --> 00:19:32,780
Slurping down noodles like that.

422
00:19:32,910 --> 00:19:34,020
You are not ladylike at all.

423
00:19:34,060 --> 00:19:35,520
It'd be weird if someone liked you.

424
00:19:35,560 --> 00:19:36,340
Just like you.

425
00:19:36,870 --> 00:19:37,820
Just like you.

426
00:19:38,990 --> 00:19:39,820
Well.

427
00:19:40,670 --> 00:19:42,780
Jing Xichi and Song Cong

428
00:19:42,870 --> 00:19:44,390
are around you all the time.

429
00:19:44,540 --> 00:19:45,100
Why don't

430
00:19:45,100 --> 00:19:46,300
they like you?

431
00:19:49,390 --> 00:19:50,060
That makes sense.

432
00:19:51,390 --> 00:19:52,190
They must

433
00:19:52,710 --> 00:19:54,430
not see you as a girl.

434
00:19:54,950 --> 00:19:55,710
Dad.

435
00:19:56,670 --> 00:19:58,020
Mom says I'm not even a girl.

436
00:19:58,190 --> 00:19:59,260
Can't you stop talking?

437
00:19:59,260 --> 00:20:00,540
My daughter is wonderful!

438
00:20:00,670 --> 00:20:01,820
She's beautiful and nice.

439
00:20:01,820 --> 00:20:02,910
Look at the way you eat.

440
00:20:03,060 --> 00:20:04,500
She learned it from you.

441
00:20:04,670 --> 00:20:06,020
Still, no dating!

442
00:20:07,340 --> 00:20:08,390
Don't listen to him.

443
00:20:12,430 --> 00:20:12,910
Dad.

444
00:20:13,900 --> 00:20:15,220
Are you done eating?

445
00:20:15,870 --> 00:20:16,740
It's all yours.

446
00:20:16,950 --> 00:20:17,910
Take this big bowl.

447
00:20:32,230 --> 00:20:34,150
Have some vitamin C after your meal.

448
00:20:34,150 --> 00:20:35,260
Mom, I can't eat anymore.

449
00:20:35,260 --> 00:20:36,300
Eat slowly.

450
00:20:36,390 --> 00:20:36,920
Oh, right.

451
00:20:36,950 --> 00:20:38,320
Since it's back-to-school season,

452
00:20:38,360 --> 00:20:39,260
book your ticket soon

453
00:20:39,390 --> 00:20:40,740
or it'll be too late.

454
00:20:41,190 --> 00:20:41,710
Got it.

455
00:20:42,300 --> 00:20:42,950
By the way,

456
00:20:43,260 --> 00:20:44,470
Aunt Hao Mei told me

457
00:20:44,470 --> 00:20:46,300
Song Cong is heading to school early.

458
00:20:46,390 --> 00:20:47,230
Is Jing Xichi

459
00:20:47,300 --> 00:20:48,100
going with him?

460
00:20:49,950 --> 00:20:51,190
I don't know.

461
00:20:52,390 --> 00:20:53,500
Aren't you always

462
00:20:53,540 --> 00:20:54,710
hanging out with him?

463
00:20:55,670 --> 00:20:57,020
He's been disappearing lately.

464
00:20:57,020 --> 00:20:58,470
I have no idea what he's up to.

465
00:20:59,630 --> 00:21:00,390
Huan'er,

466
00:21:02,060 --> 00:21:03,990
I have something to discuss with you.

467
00:21:04,630 --> 00:21:06,340
It's your first time
going to university.

468
00:21:06,340 --> 00:21:07,910
What about us going with you?

469
00:21:07,950 --> 00:21:08,580
Yeah, yeah.

470
00:21:08,670 --> 00:21:09,580
No way!

471
00:21:09,630 --> 00:21:10,100
Why not?

472
00:21:10,100 --> 00:21:10,820
Dad, Mom,

473
00:21:11,100 --> 00:21:12,230
none of my classmates

474
00:21:12,280 --> 00:21:13,340
go with their parents.

475
00:21:13,340 --> 00:21:14,580
That's fine, we can.

476
00:21:14,580 --> 00:21:15,190
How do you know

477
00:21:15,200 --> 00:21:16,300
no one's parents are going?

478
00:21:16,300 --> 00:21:17,700
Xinyan isn't going with her parents.

479
00:21:17,700 --> 00:21:18,060
Dad, Mom.

480
00:21:18,190 --> 00:21:18,670
We can go.

481
00:21:18,670 --> 00:21:20,150
At least let me spend time with you.

482
00:21:20,300 --> 00:21:21,670
I'm going to university

483
00:21:21,700 --> 00:21:22,940
to learn to live independently.

484
00:21:22,980 --> 00:21:23,680
Really!

485
00:21:27,260 --> 00:21:27,950
Help me!

486
00:21:38,992 --> 00:21:42,260
(139088 Tianhe Railway)

487
00:21:47,820 --> 00:21:49,460
(It's almost time to enter university.)

488
00:21:49,480 --> 00:21:50,600
(When are you leaving?)

489
00:21:53,420 --> 00:21:54,300
(Not decided yet.)

490
00:21:59,340 --> 00:21:59,950
(Are you free?)

491
00:22:00,120 --> 00:22:01,710
(Come and meet me at our secret base.)

492
00:22:03,470 --> 00:22:05,430
(He finally remembered me.)

493
00:22:07,390 --> 00:22:08,150
(What's up?)

494
00:22:10,520 --> 00:22:11,910
(I have something to tell you.)

495
00:22:12,000 --> 00:22:13,740
(Let's talk about it when we meet.)

496
00:22:23,910 --> 00:22:24,500
Mom,

497
00:22:24,740 --> 00:22:26,100
I'm going out for a while.

498
00:22:30,390 --> 00:22:31,740
Jing Xichi,

499
00:22:31,980 --> 00:22:33,300
I sent you so many messages,

500
00:22:33,340 --> 00:22:34,220
but you didn't reply.

501
00:22:34,240 --> 00:22:35,860
And you're finally
willing to contact me.

502
00:22:36,910 --> 00:22:37,470
What happens?

503
00:22:46,670 --> 00:22:47,300
What is this?

504
00:22:47,860 --> 00:22:49,400
The money from selling our books.

505
00:22:49,870 --> 00:22:51,100
Qi Qi, Xinyan,

506
00:22:51,230 --> 00:22:51,950
and Song Cong

507
00:22:51,990 --> 00:22:53,060
have already taken theirs.

508
00:22:53,520 --> 00:22:54,390
You're the last one.

509
00:22:54,820 --> 00:22:55,950
That much?

510
00:23:00,300 --> 00:23:01,500
Did you call me here

511
00:23:02,630 --> 00:23:03,670
just to give me money?

512
00:23:05,870 --> 00:23:06,340
Yeah.

513
00:23:11,470 --> 00:23:13,150
We're going to university soon.

514
00:23:15,870 --> 00:23:17,100
Don't you have

515
00:23:17,430 --> 00:23:18,670
anything else to say?

516
00:23:23,540 --> 00:23:24,390
I mean,

517
00:23:24,820 --> 00:23:26,710
I haven't seen you these past few days.

518
00:23:26,840 --> 00:23:28,340
I have no idea what you've been up to.

519
00:23:30,950 --> 00:23:32,950
I was selling books,

520
00:23:34,150 --> 00:23:36,780
working on my website,

521
00:23:37,470 --> 00:23:38,740
and handling all sorts

522
00:23:38,740 --> 00:23:39,430
of random things.

523
00:23:42,870 --> 00:23:43,540
It's fine.

524
00:23:43,950 --> 00:23:44,710
Anyway,

525
00:23:44,990 --> 00:23:45,870
we'll see each other

526
00:23:45,870 --> 00:23:46,950
during school breaks.

527
00:23:47,300 --> 00:23:48,430
If you need anything,

528
00:23:48,470 --> 00:23:49,470
just call me.

529
00:24:02,100 --> 00:24:03,300
Honestly,

530
00:24:04,470 --> 00:24:05,100
when I got

531
00:24:05,100 --> 00:24:06,630
my admission letter,

532
00:24:07,710 --> 00:24:08,820
I was really happy.

533
00:24:11,340 --> 00:24:12,710
But the moment I realized

534
00:24:12,990 --> 00:24:14,500
we were all going our separate ways

535
00:24:15,100 --> 00:24:16,580
and living in different cities...

536
00:24:18,870 --> 00:24:20,190
I couldn't feel happy anymore.

537
00:24:31,230 --> 00:24:31,950
Do you think

538
00:24:34,340 --> 00:24:35,710
we will

539
00:24:36,780 --> 00:24:38,580
slowly lose touch?

540
00:24:40,740 --> 00:24:41,430
Why?

541
00:24:42,870 --> 00:24:43,630
You

542
00:24:44,740 --> 00:24:45,950
can't bear to leave me?

543
00:24:49,340 --> 00:24:50,150
Yeah.

544
00:24:50,340 --> 00:24:51,580
I can't bear to leave you.

545
00:24:55,990 --> 00:24:56,430
Alright.

546
00:24:56,740 --> 00:24:57,260
I get to go.

547
00:25:00,190 --> 00:25:00,710
Oh yeah.

548
00:25:01,390 --> 00:25:02,260
Well...

549
00:25:02,470 --> 00:25:03,470
Before we part,

550
00:25:04,560 --> 00:25:05,780
let's have a hug.

551
00:25:22,500 --> 00:25:23,260
I'm leaving.

552
00:25:27,780 --> 00:25:28,430
Thank you.

553
00:25:29,870 --> 00:25:30,560
Not a big deal.

554
00:26:12,740 --> 00:26:14,190
We're not that far apart.

555
00:26:14,230 --> 00:26:15,640
(Tianhe No.3 Central Hospital Compound)
I'll come back soon.

556
00:26:15,680 --> 00:26:16,940
Driver, can you open the boot?

557
00:26:17,780 --> 00:26:18,580
Make sure

558
00:26:18,670 --> 00:26:19,580
to keep your ID safe.

559
00:26:19,630 --> 00:26:20,910
Keep your wallet secure.

560
00:26:21,060 --> 00:26:21,580
And,

561
00:26:21,680 --> 00:26:23,160
as soon as you get off the train,

562
00:26:23,180 --> 00:26:24,060
call Mom. Got it?

563
00:26:24,060 --> 00:26:25,190
Yes, I'll text you.

564
00:26:25,300 --> 00:26:25,710
Huan'er,

565
00:26:25,820 --> 00:26:27,150
do you have enough phone credit?

566
00:26:27,190 --> 00:26:28,300
If not, I can top it up.

567
00:26:28,360 --> 00:26:30,500
You just topped it up
with a hundred yesterday.

568
00:26:30,540 --> 00:26:31,180
Remember,

569
00:26:31,230 --> 00:26:32,140
when you get there,

570
00:26:32,200 --> 00:26:33,740
eat well and buy whatever you need.

571
00:26:33,920 --> 00:26:35,680
Don't worry,
I won't let myself go hungry.

572
00:26:35,700 --> 00:26:36,100
Oh yeah...

573
00:26:36,100 --> 00:26:37,020
Stop nagging.

574
00:26:37,100 --> 00:26:38,380
She still has to catch the train.

575
00:26:38,400 --> 00:26:39,260
If you hold her up,

576
00:26:39,740 --> 00:26:40,540
she'll miss it.

577
00:26:40,540 --> 00:26:41,150
Wait a second.

578
00:26:41,430 --> 00:26:41,950
I want a hug.

579
00:26:45,060 --> 00:26:45,470
Dad.

580
00:26:45,960 --> 00:26:46,990
Take care of yourself.

581
00:26:47,470 --> 00:26:48,710
One more hug for me.

582
00:26:48,960 --> 00:26:49,950
Alright, didn't you say

583
00:26:49,990 --> 00:26:50,740
she was in a hurry?

584
00:26:50,870 --> 00:26:51,710
Go on, go on.

585
00:26:52,430 --> 00:26:52,990
